AS TO COUNT 1 AND AMENDED COUNT 3:
Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he/she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and as amended and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.

AS TO COUNT 2:
State's motion to dismiss and read-in count 2 granted by the court.

Case adjourned for sentencing hearing in Branch 10.
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may not possess firearms.
Court advised defendant that he may not vote until civil rights are restored.

AS TO COUNT 3:
On motion of the State, Court ordered charge amended to Exposing Genitals to a Child, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 948.10(1)(a), a Class I Felony.
